						<summary>

						<p>On a slab standing in a field.</p>						

						<p>[Dēvarāya], Circa 14th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This gives the genealogical account of the Vijayanagara kings, in the course of which are mentioned Bukkarāya, Harihara, Vijaya-bhūpati and Dēvarāya. It seems to record a gift to the god Rāmachandra. It also mentions the village Chittārige, situated in Honnāvura-dēśa, and the <hi rend="italic">āchārya</hi> Rāmachandra-yatīśvara. The inscription is badly damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
